methods.compile:
:param expression: java.lang.String
:param filename: java.lang.String
:param mode: java.lang.String
:return: org.jpy.PyObject
methods.dict:
Create a new dictionary.

:return: (org.jpy.PyObject) the dictionary
methods.dir:
Attempt to return a list of valid attributes for that object.

:param pyObject: (org.jpy.PyObject) - the python object
:return: (org.jpy.PyObject) the list of valid attributes for the object
methods.len:
Get the length (the number of items) of an object. The argument may be a sequence (such as a string, bytes,
 tuple, list, or range) or a collection (such as a dictionary, set, or frozen set).

:param pyObject: (org.jpy.PyObject) - the python object
:return: (int) the length (the number of items) of an object
methods.memoryview:
Create a memoryview that references obj. obj must support the buffer protocol.

:param pyObject: (org.jpy.PyObject) - the python object.
:return: (org.jpy.PyObject) the memoryview
